WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:01.570
To create a test in Blackboard,

1
00:00:01.730 --> 00:00:02.890
click the plus button,

2
00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:04.219
followed by create.

3
00:00:04.570 --> 00:00:05.489
On the content menu,

4
00:00:05.610 --> 00:00:06.590
select test.

5
00:00:07.050 --> 00:00:07.869
On the test page,

6
00:00:08.140 --> 00:00:10.630
choose a name that students can easily identify,

7
00:00:11.090 --> 00:00:13.310
then click the plus button in the center of the screen.

8
00:00:14.420 --> 00:00:16.629
There are several options for question types from

9
00:00:16.629 --> 00:00:19.049
multiple choice to short answer to essay.

10
00:00:19.510 --> 00:00:23.049
Questions can be auto generated for each style if desired,

11
00:00:23.389 --> 00:00:26.090
or instructors can type in their own questions.

12
00:00:26.629 --> 00:00:27.590
For this example,

13
00:00:27.829 --> 00:00:30.370
we will auto generate questions using AI.

14
00:00:30.909 --> 00:00:33.709
Type in a topic covered or select content from the course

15
00:00:33.709 --> 00:00:36.889
for AI to scan for guidance and then generate questions.

16
00:00:37.759 --> 00:00:40.189
There are different style options for the questions,

17
00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:42.319
such as application questions,

18
00:00:42.479 --> 00:00:43.900
identify or create,

19
00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:47.479
as well as the ability to change the difficulty level of the question.

20
00:00:59.630 --> 00:01:01.180
Once the questions are generated,

21
00:01:01.349 --> 00:01:02.849
select the ones to be used.

22
00:01:05.949 --> 00:01:10.250
Change the availability of the assessment to visible to students and click save.